    "department": "Growth",
    "description": "Solution Architect\n\n\nAbout Smallest.ai http://Smallest.ai\nAt smallest.ai http://smallest.ai, we’re building the future of customer conversations with AI-powered voice agents. Our mission is to help enterprises in BFSI, Financial Services, and Fintech automate complex interactions with speed and empathy. With strong investor backing, we are scaling rapidly across India and the US.\n\n\nJob Summary\nAs a Solution Architect, you will translate customer needs into scalable AI solutions. You will design conversational journeys, define integration requirements, and ensure what’s promised is what ships—partnering closely with Implementation Engineers, Product, and Sales. This role is ideal for someone who enjoys being hands-on with technology while directly shaping customer success.\n\n\nKey Responsibilities\n• Lead discovery and solution scoping sessions with Indian enterprise clients.\n• Design conversational flows and align internal/external stakeholders on approach.\n• Create lightweight documentation (flows, assumptions, timelines) and secure approvals.\n• Guide data and integration strategy; identify reusable patterns for scale.\n• Partner with Delivery and Implementation Engineers on acceptance criteria and change\nmanagement.\n• Provide feedback to Product/Engineering teams based on customer needs.\nRequirements – What We’re Looking For\n• Enjoy working directly with customers, iterating on solutions, and providing tailored support.\n• Passion for AI, emerging tech, and voice-first products.\n• Proficiency in Python with strong debugging and integration skills.\n• Understanding of common integration patterns (APIs, middleware, enterprise SaaS systems).\n• Experience working with enterprise clients in BFSI, Fintech, or Financial Services.\n• Strong empathy for customers, sales, and product teams.\n• Excellent personal presentation, communication, and client-servicing skills.\n\n\nSuccess Metrics\n• Clear, approved solution scopes before build.\n• Minimal changes during implementation.\n• High customer satisfaction and seamless delivery handoffs",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
